<section id="fs-id1170571539130" class="section-exercises">
<p id="fs-id1170571539134">In the following exercises, express the limits as integrals.</p>

<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170571539139">
<p id="fs-id1170571539142"><m>\lim_{n\to \infty }\displaystyle{\sum_{i=1}^n  (x_i^* )\Delta x} </m> over <m>[1,3]</m></p>
</statement>


<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170571543215">
<p id="fs-id1170571543217"><m>\lim_{n\to \infty }\displaystyle{\sum_{i=1}^n  (5<m:msup>(x_i^* )2</m:msup>-3<m:msup>(x_i^* )3</m:msup>)\Delta x} </m> over <m>[0,2]</m></p>
</statement>
<solution id="fs-id1170572456369">
<p id="fs-id1170572456371"><m>\displaystyle{\int_{0}^{2} (5x^2-3x^3)dx} </m></p>
</solution>


<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170572396476">
<p id="fs-id1170572396479"><m>\lim_{n\to \infty }\displaystyle{\sum_{i=1}^n  <m:msup>\sin2</m:msup>(2\pix_i^* )\Delta x} </m> over <m>[0,1]</m></p>
</statement>


<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170571580958">
<p id="fs-id1170571580960"><m>\lim_{n\to \infty }\displaystyle{\sum_{i=1}^n  <m:msup>\text{ cos }2</m:msup>(2\pix_i^* )\Delta x} </m> over <m>[0,1]</m></p>
</statement>
<solution id="fs-id1170572218599">
<p id="fs-id1170572218601"><m>\displaystyle{\int_{0}^{1} <m:msup>\text{ cos }2</m:msup>(2\pix)dx} </m></p>
</solution>

<p id="fs-id1170572218644">In the following exercises, given <emphasis effect="italics">L<sub>n</sub></emphasis> or <emphasis effect="italics">R<sub>n</sub></emphasis> as indicated, express their limits as <m>n\to \infty </m> as definite integrals, identifying the correct intervals.</p>

<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170572386107">
<p id="fs-id1170572386109"><m>L_n=\frac{1}{n}\displaystyle{\sum_{i=1}^n  \frac{i-1n}} </m></p>
</statement>


<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170572386184">
<p id="fs-id1170572386186"><m>R_n=\frac{1}{n}\displaystyle{\sum_{i=1}^n  \frac{i}{n}} </m></p>
</statement>
<solution id="fs-id1170572643208">
<p id="fs-id1170572643210"><m>\displaystyle{\int_{0}^{1} xdx} </m></p>
</solution>


<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170572643237">
<p id="fs-id1170572643239"><m>L_n=\frac{2}{n}\displaystyle{\sum_{i=1}^n  (1+2\frac{i-1n})} </m></p>
</statement>


<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170572373704">
<p id="fs-id1170572373706"><m>R_n=\frac{3}{n}\displaystyle{\sum_{i=1}^n  (3+3\frac{i}{n})} </m></p>
</statement>
<solution id="fs-id1170571710640">
<p id="fs-id1170571710642"><m>\displaystyle{\int_{3}^{6} xdx} </m></p>
</solution>


<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170571710670">
<p id="fs-id1170571710672"><m>L_n=\frac{2\pin}\displaystyle{\sum_{i=1}^n  2\pi\frac{i-1n}\text{ cos }(2\pi\frac{i-1n})} </m></p>
</statement>


<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170572399037">
<p id="fs-id1170572399039"><m>R_n=\frac{1}{n}\displaystyle{\sum_{i=1}^n  (1+\frac{i}{n})\text{ log }(<m:msup>(1+\frac{i}{n})2</m:msup>)} </m></p>
</statement>
<solution id="fs-id1170572168726">
<p id="fs-id1170572168728"><m>\displaystyle{\int_{1}^{2} x \text{ log }(x^2)dx} </m></p>
</solution>

<p id="fs-id1170572168771">In the following exercises, evaluate the integrals of the functions graphed using the formulas for areas of triangles and circles, and subtracting the areas below the <m>x</m>-axis.</p>

<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170572168783">
<description>"A graph containing the upper half of three circles on the x axis. The first has center at (1,0) and radius one. It corresponds to the function sqrt(2x – x^2) over [0,2]. The second has center at (4,0) and radius two. It corresponds to the function sqrt(-12 + 8x – x^2) over [2,6]. The last has center at (9,0) and radius three. It corresponds to the function sqrt(-72 + 18x – x^2) over [6,12]. All three semi circles are shaded – the area under the curve and above the x axis.">
<image source="CNX_Calc_Figure_05_02_201.jpg" width="50%">

</statement>


<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170572629210">
<description>"A graph of three isosceles triangles corresponding to the functions 1 - |x-1| over [0,2], 2 - |x-4| over [2,4], and 3 - |x-9| over [6,12]. The first triangle has endpoints at (0,0), (2,0), and (1,1). The second triangle has endpoints at (2,0), (6,0), and (4,2). The last has endpoints at (6,0), (12,0), and (9,3). All three are shaded.">
