<p id="fs-id1170571638103">In the following exercises, given that <m>\displaystyle{\int_{0}^{1} xdx} =\frac{1}{2},\displaystyle{\int_{0}^{1} x^2dx} =\frac{1}{3},</m> and <m>\displaystyle{\int_{0}^{1} x^3dx} =\frac{1}{4},</m> compute the integrals.</p>

