<p id="fs-id1170572558112">In the following exercises, use the <xref ref="fs-id1170571653089">comparison theorem</url>.</p>

<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170572558117">
<p id="fs-id1170572558119">Show that <m>\displaystyle{\int_{0}^{3} (x^2-6x+9)dx} \geq 0.</m></p>
</statement>


<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170571813998">
<p id="fs-id1170571814000">Show that <m>\displaystyle{\int_{-2}^{3}(x-3)}{(x+2)dx} \leq 0.</m></p>
</statement>
<solution id="fs-id1170572307625">
<p id="fs-id1170572307627">The integrand is negative over <m>[-2,3].</m></p>
</solution>


<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170572307652">
<p id="fs-id1170572307654">Show that <m>\displaystyle{\int_{0}^{1} \sqrt{1+x^3}dx} \leq \displaystyle{\int_{0}^{1} \sqrt{1+x^2}dx} .</m></p>
</statement>


<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170572480473">
<p id="fs-id1170572480475">Show that <m>\displaystyle{\int_{1}^{2} \sqrt{1+x}dx} \leq \displaystyle{\int_{1}^{2} \sqrt{1+x^2}dx} .</m></p>
</statement>
<solution id="fs-id1170572624742">
<p id="fs-id1170572624744"><m>x\leq x^2</m> over <m>[1,2],</m> so <m>\sqrt{1+x}\leq \sqrt{1+x^2}</m> over <m>[1,2].</m></p>
</solution>


<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170572218472">
<p id="fs-id1170572218474">Show that <m>\displaystyle{<m:msubsup>∫0\pi\text{ / }2</m:msubsup>\sin tdt} \geq \frac{\pi}{4}.</m> <m>\(Hint\text{ : } \sin t\geq \frac{2t\pi}</m> over <m>[0,\frac{\pi}{2}]\text{ ) }</m></p>
</statement>


<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170571712390">
<p id="fs-id1170571712392">Show that <m>\displaystyle{<m:msubsup>∫-\pi\text{ / }4}{\pi\text{ / }4</m:msubsup>\text{ cos } tdt} \geq \pi\sqrt{2}\text{ / }4.</m></p>
</statement>
<solution id="fs-id1170571712449">
<p id="fs-id1170571712451"><m>\text{ cos }(t)\geq \frac{\sqrt{2}2}.</m> Multiply by the length of the interval to get the inequality.</p>
</solution>

<p id="fs-id1170571629661">In the following exercises, find the average value f_{\text{ave}}  of <m>f</m> between <m>a</m> and <m>b</m>, and find a point <m>c</m>, where <m>f(c)=<m:msub>f\text{ ave }</m:msub>.</m></p>

<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170571629716">
<p id="fs-id1170571629718"><m>f(x)=x^2,a=-1,b=1</m></p>
</statement>


<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170571542812">
<p id="fs-id1170571542814"><m>f(x)=x^5,a=-1,b=1</m></p>
</statement>
<solution id="fs-id1170571542854">
<p id="fs-id1170571542856"><m><m:msub>f\text{ ave }</m:msub>=0;c=0</m></p>
</solution>


<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170571542884">
<p id="fs-id1170571542886"><m>f(x)=\sqrt{4-x^2},a=0,b=2</m></p>
</statement>


<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170571624147">
<p id="fs-id1170571624149"><m>f(x)=(3-|x|),a=-3,b=3</m></p>
</statement>
<solution id="fs-id1170571698166">
<p id="fs-id1170571698168"><m>\frac{3}{2}</m> when <m>c=\pm \frac{3}{2}</m></p>
</solution>


<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170571698196">
<p id="fs-id1170571698199"><m>f(x)=\sin x,a=0,b=2\pi</m></p>
</statement>


<!-- Move title outside statement--> <statement id="fs-id1170572309562">
<p id="fs-id1170572309564"><m>f(x)=\text{ cos } x,a=0,b=2\pi</m></p>
</statement>
<solution id="fs-id1170572309608">
